## Page Types & Front Matter

### Overview Page (`index.md`)

```yaml
---
layout: workshop
---
```

The landing page should include:
- Workshop overview and learning objectives
- How to use this workshop (navigation instructions)
- Skill progression table mapping levels to skills gained
- Curriculum table with links to each step
- Quick start commands to set up the development environment
- Requirements and prerequisites

### Step Pages (`workshop/level-N/README.md`)

```yaml
---
layout: step
title: "Step Title"
step_number: N           # 0 for setup, 1+ for content steps
permalink: /steps/N/     # Must match step_number
---
```

Content guidelines for step pages:
- Start with a brief intro paragraph explaining what this step covers
- Use `##` for major sections, `###` for subsections
- Include code blocks with language identifiers (` ```bash `, ` ```python `, ` ```yaml `, etc.)
- Use callouts for tips and warnings (see Content Writing Rules below)
- Include hands-on exercises with clear, numbered instructions
- End with a summary or "What you accomplished" section

### Cheatsheet Pages (`workshop/level-N/CHEATSHEET.md`)

```yaml
---
layout: cheatsheet
title: "Level N — Quick Reference"
parent_step: N           # Must match the step_number of the parent step
permalink: /cheatsheet/N/
---
```

Cheatsheet content should include:
- Command tables with descriptions
- Syntax summaries and quick reference material
- Common patterns and examples
- Troubleshooting tips for the parent step

### Setup Page (`setup.md`)

```yaml
---
layout: step
title: "Setup & Installation"
step_number: 0
permalink: /setup/
---
```

The setup page is step 0. It should cover environment setup, tool installation, repository cloning, and any initial configuration needed before starting the workshop.

