## Directory Structure

```
{REPO_NAME}/
├── _config.yml                    # Theme configuration
├── index.md                       # Landing page (layout: workshop)
├── setup.md                       # Setup guide (layout: step, step_number: 0)
├── workshop/
│   ├── level-1/
│   │   ├── README.md              # Step content (layout: step, step_number: 1)
│   │   ├── CHEATSHEET.md          # Quick ref (layout: cheatsheet, parent_step: 1)
│   │   └── sample-app/            # Practice code for this level
│   ├── level-2/
│   │   ├── README.md
│   │   ├── CHEATSHEET.md
│   │   └── sample-app/
│   └── ...
├── .github/
│   ├── workflows/
│   │   └── deploy-pages.yml       # GitHub Pages deployment
│   └── copilot-instructions.md    # This file
└── README.md                      # Repository README (not rendered by theme)
```

Key conventions:
- Steps live in `workshop/level-N/` directories, numbered sequentially starting at 1.
- Setup is always `setup.md` at the root with `step_number: 0`.
- Each level directory may contain a `sample-app/` folder with practice code.
- The `index.md` at the root is the workshop landing page.

