## Adding New Steps

When asked to add a new step to the workshop:

1. **Create the step page** at `workshop/level-{N}/README.md`:
   ```yaml
   ---
   layout: step
   title: "Step Title"
   step_number: N
   permalink: /steps/N/
   ---
   ```

2. **Create the cheatsheet** at `workshop/level-{N}/CHEATSHEET.md`:
   ```yaml
   ---
   layout: cheatsheet
   title: "Level N — Quick Reference"
   parent_step: N
   permalink: /cheatsheet/N/
   ---
   ```

3. **Optionally create a sample-app directory** at `workshop/level-{N}/sample-app/` for starter code, solution code, or any practice files for that step.

4. **Sidebar navigation updates automatically** — The theme discovers step pages by their `layout: step` front matter and `step_number` values. No manual navigation configuration or linking is needed.

5. **Update `index.md`** — Add the new step to the curriculum table on the landing page so readers can see the full workshop outline.

